data.meta_description: Karl Egil Aubert, (19 August 1924-21 August 1990)  He was a Norwegian mathematician. He took his doctor's degree in Paris in 1957, and stayed at the Institute for Advanced Study in Princeton from 1958 to 1960. From 1962 to 1990 he was a professor at the University of Oslo. He chaired the Norwegian Mathematics Society...
